This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new adversarial training method based on a general learning-to-learn framework. It also involves the learning of a robust classifier, which is a common topic in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100 datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as adversarial training is a popular topic in AI research. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper deals with adversarial attacks and defenses, which are important topics in security research. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed method involves the learning of an optimizer, which is parametrized as a convolutional neural network.
